      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry and chill, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs with some pea-sized pieces of butter remaining. Add 5 to 7 tablespoons of ice-cold water, a tablespoon at a time, mixing with a fork until the dough just comes together. Divide into two discs (one slightly larger). Wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. This pastry does not use ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "blind baking",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp5q86lz0000i0v4jdo0db27"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": it bakes through under the hot fruit filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toss the sliced {{peaches}} with the {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, {{lemon-juice}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Leave to macerate for 15 minutes. Roll the larger pastry disc on a lightly floured surface to a circle about 30 cm in diameter. Line the pie dish, leaving overhang. Fill with the peach mixture. Roll the second disc and lay it over the filling. Trim to 2 cm overhang, crimp the edges together, and cut 5 vents in the top crust.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 45 to 55 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Brush the top crust with the {{eggs}} wash and scatter the {{demerara-sugar}} over. Bake for 20 minutes at 200°C, then reduce to 180°C and bake for a further 25 to 30 minutes until the crust is deep golden and the juices are bubbling through the vents. Cool on a rack for at least 1 hour before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
